1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the achievable rates of a family of codes, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a communication protocol based on codes with expandable message space, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with wireless systems, which is a topic relevant to systems and control. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication, which is a topic relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not directly related to multimedia, the paper deals with communication channels, which is a topic relevant to multimedia.
